The paper discusses techniques for efficient computation of eigenvalue problems and kernel learning problems, which are typically studied in numerical analysis (cs.NA) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the CUR matrix decomposition, which is a data structure used in data science (cs.DS). The paper proposes a novel combination of existing methods, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SI) techniques.
